    {
        "text": "My father, José Perez,\ndied as an indirect result",
        "start": 9.745,
        "duration": 4.395
    },
    {
        "text": "of Hurricane Maria.",
        "start": 14.14,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "He is shoe No. 399.",
        "start": 15.98,
        "duration": 3.667
    },
    {
        "text": "No. 2851.",
        "start": 22.857,
        "duration": 3.233
    },
    {
        "text": "My mother, Juanita\nMélendez Betancourt",
        "start": 26.09,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "died of a heart attack\ndue to complications",
        "start": 28.18,
        "duration": 2.603
    },
    {
        "text": "from Hurricane Maria.",
        "start": 30.783,
        "duration": 1.863
    },
    {
        "text": "I cry because it’s hard\nto see a system erasing",
        "start": 50.06,
        "duration": 6.27
    },
    {
        "text": "the pain of the people.",
        "start": 56.33,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "You cannot erase that.",
        "start": 57.62,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "And you have to be respectful\nwith the dead ones.",
        "start": 59.04,
        "duration": 2.455
    },
    {
        "text": "Shoe No. 2231.",
        "start": 61.495,
        "duration": 3.445
    },
    {
        "text": "My grandmother spent Hurricane\nIrma and Hurricane Maria",
        "start": 64.94,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "at the hospital.",
        "start": 69.26,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "She was a patient\non hemodialysis.",
        "start": 71.33,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "In this moment, 2018,\nwe’re having “desaparecidos,”",
        "start": 74.32,
        "duration": 4.36
    },
    {
        "text": "thousand of people who \nare completely disappeared,",
        "start": 78.68,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "invisible to the system.",
        "start": 81.14,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "We want to make a closure.",
        "start": 82.97,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "We want to finish.",
        "start": 84.56,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "We want to close that pain.",
        "start": 85.41,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Jiram Perez — \nshoe No. 2860.",
        "start": 88.35,
        "duration": 4.552
    },
    {
        "text": "My grandfather passed away\nin the horrible aftermath",
        "start": 92.902,
        "duration": 3.864
    },
    {
        "text": "of Hurricane Maria.",
        "start": 96.766,
        "duration": 1.932
    },
    {
        "text": "These are human beings.",
        "start": 98.698,
        "duration": 0.972
    },
    {
        "text": "They are not just\nnumbers or statistics.",
        "start": 99.67,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "They have faces.",
        "start": 102.23,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "They lived.",
        "start": 103.11,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "They loved.",
        "start": 104.4,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "They are gone.",
        "start": 105.09,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "They are missed.",
        "start": 107.61,
        "duration": 1.271
    },
    {
        "text": "[wind blowing]",
        "start": 108.881,
        "duration": 3.367
    },
    {
        "text": "We demand the\ngovernor of Puerto Rico",
        "start": 118.26,
        "duration": 1.684
    },
    {
        "text": "to be prepared for the\nnext hurricane season.",
        "start": 119.944,
        "duration": 5.186
    },
    {
        "text": "We demand that President Trump\nto apologize to the country",
        "start": 125.13,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "of throwing towels.",
        "start": 129.11,
        "duration": 1.529
    },
    {
        "text": "If you look at a real\ncatastrophe like Katrina —",
        "start": 130.639,
        "duration": 4.061
    },
    {
        "text": "16 people versus\nin the thousands.",
        "start": 134.7,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "And not accepting that\nwe were having thousands",
        "start": 137.48,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "of victims in the island.",
        "start": 139.66,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "I say to the politicians\nin the States to be careful,",
        "start": 141.65,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "and to take Puerto\nRican and Puerto Rican",
        "start": 144.69,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "respect as something serious.",
        "start": 146.84,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "We have a vote there\nin the States.",
